IPS Web – Security Filter Test (Quick Instructions)

We added a URL security filter to block malicious query parameters (XSS attempts). Please run the tests below in DEV/CAT.

Use this base page:

https://<env-host>/IPSWeb/verification_user_information.xhtml


⸻

1. Normal Flow (Baseline)

Steps

Open the page normally and go through the regular flow.

Expected

Application works normally. No errors.

⸻

2. Script Injection Test

Open:

https://<env-host>/IPSWeb/verification_user_information.xhtml?test=%3Cscript%3E

Expected

Request should be blocked and show a security error page (not a server 500).

⸻

3. JavaScript Injection

Open:

https://<env-host>/IPSWeb/verification_user_information.xhtml?cmd=alert(1)

Expected

Blocked with security error page.

⸻

4. Event Handler Injection

Open:

https://<env-host>/IPSWeb/verification_user_information.xhtml?param=onerror=alert(1)

Expected

Blocked with security error page.

⸻

5. Valid Parameter (Should Pass)

Open:

https://<env-host>/IPSWeb/verification_user_information.xhtml?do=start

Expected

Page loads normally.

⸻

6. Oversized Parameter Test

In browser console run:

var base = window.location.origin + "/IPSWeb/verification_user_information.xhtml";
var large = "a".repeat(2050);
window.open(base + "?test=" + large);

Expected

Blocked with security error page.

